sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as Client / Controller
    participant MM1 as ModelMesh Pod A<br/>8033/TCP gRPC TLS
    participant MM2 as ModelMesh Pod B<br/>8080/TCP Litelinks TLS
    participant Runtime as Model Runtime<br/>8085/TCP or UDS<br/>plaintext
    participant etcd as etcd Cluster<br/>2379/TCP gRPC TLS

    Note over Client,etcd: Flow 1: Model Inference Request

    Client->>MM1: gRPC Inference Request<br/>Port 8033, TLS, mTLS optional
    MM1->>MM1: Check local model cache
    alt Model loaded locally
        MM1->>Runtime: gRPC inference<br/>Port 8085/UDS, plaintext
        Runtime-->>MM1: Inference result
    else Model on another pod
        MM1->>MM2: Forward via Litelinks<br/>Port 8080, TLS, Cert-based
        MM2->>Runtime: gRPC inference<br/>Port 8085/UDS, plaintext
        Runtime-->>MM2: Inference result
        MM2-->>MM1: Response via Litelinks
    end
    MM1-->>Client: gRPC Response<br/>TLS

    Note over Client,etcd: Flow 2: Model Registration and Loading

    Client->>MM1: registerModel RPC<br/>Port 8033, TLS
    MM1->>etcd: Store model record<br/>Port 2379, TLS, Cert auth
    etcd-->>MM1: Ack
    MM1->>Runtime: loadModel RPC<br/>Port 8085/UDS, plaintext
    Runtime-->>MM1: Load result (size, maxConcurrency)
    MM1->>etcd: Update model status<br/>Port 2379, TLS, Cert auth
    etcd-->>MM1: Ack
    MM1-->>Client: Registration response

    Note over Client,etcd: Flow 3: Pod Startup and Runtime Discovery

    MM1->>Runtime: runtimeStatus RPC<br/>Port 8085/UDS, plaintext
    Runtime-->>MM1: Runtime capabilities<br/>(capacity, model types)
    MM1->>etcd: Register instance<br/>Port 2379, TLS, Cert auth
    etcd-->>MM1: Ack

    Note right of MM1: Health probes begin
    Note right of MM1: Port 8089/HTTP /ready /live
